        <abstract>
            <p>Asks JL to send ten shillings for the Down Friendly Club.</p> 
<p>Has just read JL’s paper on bees and wasps [<hi rend="italic">J. Linn. Soc. Lond. (Zool.)</hi> 12 (1876): 110–39]. Is astonished by their stupidity. The experiments on colour are especially good. Suggests JL examine their retinas; sends enclosure [missing] on eyes of reptiles and birds.</p> 
        </abstract>
